{"anchor_hash": "47699f17195d53f453fbb516bcf784e197b02e591aeb8306db7c4d5a64b1e842", "app_version": "review-interface-v0", "approximate_scroll_percent": 42, "chapter_id": null, "chapter_title": null, "comment_text": "The manor should have some kind of protective or alarming zan lattice on its back gateway that Kelyra disables with her magic by draining it, which is difficult and justifies Davian (to some extent) wanting to exclude her from the combat. In general, Zan technology should be more prevalent and certainly would be seen in Clade architecture on a routine basis. But even low class people could use rough etched Zan for light, alarms, etc.", "commenter_name": "Dustin", "content_hash": "c2ac60124ad5052ea9c61ba5ad9c8701f2332f7f36a78ddf1f09993d7bc5d08c", "created_at": "2026-06-28T02:34:32.455Z", "current_file_path": "bible/locations/loc-sorevin-redbridge.md", "current_heading": "Sorevin Manor", "current_layer": "repository-file", "id": "comment-1782614072454-9d0xcm", "import_batch_id": "2026-06-29-001", "imported_at": "2026-06-29T19:49:35+00:00", "importer_version": "webapp-comment-import-v1", "initial_classification": "story-bible-question", "likely_target_id": "bible/locations/loc-sorevin-redbridge.md", "likely_target_type": "file", "normalized_id": "wc-c2ac60124ad5052e", "processing_status": "duplicate", "repo_branch": "main", "repo_commit": "c213489d3efba31aafa0287e50f83b8e94f030b5", "reviewer_session_id": "session-432bfb71-a607-43b9-bd28-0a47756c139f", "scratchpad_type": null, "selected_text": "", "source_export_file": "fractured-fate-comments-dustinr-20260629-1416-from-drive.json", "source_line_end": null, "source_line_start": null, "status": "inbox", "view_mode": "repo-browser"}
{"anchor_hash": "13c141a34e8afb05e1e498808e2b96f4ec79f552b138776d0e2ce452788de803", "app_version": "review-interface-v0", "approximate_scroll_percent": 29, "chapter_id": null, "chapter_title": null, "comment_text": "It also requires more technical ability to etch the small details that make up ancient Zan, and the materials for doing so are more expensive. So even if someone else knew what Zirene did, they wouldn’t be able to replicate what she did necessarily, and it certainly wouldn’t be cheap. See Archeon’s attempted knockoffs with their own zanwright (who in a later book will help Kelyra make more Zan-tech for anti clade activities)", "commenter_name": "Dustin", "content_hash": "064e419148366b5c39bec219f8688b5fdda2ce420806be3af34097b75f23ad07", "created_at": "2026-06-28T02:37:36.236Z", "current_file_path": "bible/magic/magic-zan-lattices.md", "current_heading": "Zän / Zä Lattices / Zänwrights", "current_layer": "repository-file", "id": "comment-1782614256236-vozds5", "import_batch_id": "2026-06-29-001", "imported_at": "2026-06-29T19:49:35+00:00", "importer_version": "webapp-comment-import-v1", "initial_classification": "continuity-question", "likely_target_id": "bible/magic/magic-zan-lattices.md", "likely_target_type": "file", "normalized_id": "wc-064e419148366b5c", "processing_status": "duplicate", "repo_branch": "main", "repo_commit": "c213489d3efba31aafa0287e50f83b8e94f030b5", "reviewer_session_id": "session-432bfb71-a607-43b9-bd28-0a47756c139f", "scratchpad_type": null, "selected_text": "", "source_export_file": "fractured-fate-comments-dustinr-20260629-1416-from-drive.json", "source_line_end": null, "source_line_start": null, "status": "inbox", "view_mode": "repo-browser"}
